    <briefdescription>
<para>Sequential Impulse contact solver for unconstrained rigid bodies. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Resolves normal and friction contact constraints using a Projected Gauss-Seidel loop with accumulated impulse clamping. Contact impulses are computed in world coordinates and applied to linear velocity (m/s) and angular velocity (rad/s).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This solver is intended for a single-threaded update loop. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="warning"><para>Inputs must be physically consistent (mass in kg, inertia in kg*m^2, time step in seconds) to avoid instability. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
